abstract: Rangers in South Africa kill three poachers in Kruger National Park, where two-thirds of nation's poaching deaths of rhinos occurred in 2014; demand for rhino horn is surging in parts of Asia where it is seen as status symbol and cure for illness.
lead_paragraph: The killings happened in Kruger National Park, where two-thirds of the nation’s poaching deaths of rhinos occurred this year, according to government figures.

headline.main: Rangers Kill Three Poachers in South Africa
